# CI/CD — GitHub Actions

This directory contains GitHub Actions workflows for validating and deploying your agent project as a Databricks Asset Bundle.

## Workflows

| File | Trigger | What it does |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `deploy-cicd.yml` | Manual | Generates project-specific workflow files. Run once per project. |
| `{{ .input_project_name }}-bundle-cicd.yml` | PR to `main`, merge to `main`, merge to `release` | Validates bundle config (CI), deploys to staging (CD on main merge), deploys to prod (CD on release merge) |
| `{{ .input_project_name }}-tests-ci.yml` | PR to `main` | Runs unit and integration tests |

## Setup

1. Create service principals for staging and prod workspaces
2. Add required secrets to your GitHub repo (see [AgentOps Setup Guide](../../docs/agentops-setup.md))
3. Enable "Read and write permissions" under Repo Settings > Actions > General > Workflow permissions
4. Run `deploy-cicd.yml` manually to generate the project workflows

## Pipeline flow

```
PR to main  →  validate bundle (staging + prod) + run tests
Merge to main  →  deploy to staging
Merge to release  →  deploy to prod
```

For details, see the [AgentOps Setup Guide](../../docs/agentops-setup.md).
